                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14119398" author="stack" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 05:47:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added in 2.3 &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-5260&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-5260&lt;/a&gt; Look for interface &lt;a href=&quot;http://grepcode.com/file/repository.cloudera.com/content/repositories/releases/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-common/2.3.0-cdh5.0.0/org/apache/hadoop/fs/HasEnhancedByteBufferAccess.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://grepcode.com/file/repository.cloudera.com/content/repositories/releases/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-common/2.3.0-cdh5.0.0/org/apache/hadoop/fs/HasEnhancedByteBufferAccess.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14163911" author="anoop.hbase" created="Wed, 8 Oct 2014 18:21:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You mean in case where we don&apos;t have the on heap L1 cache at all?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14164101" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 8 Oct 2014 20:25:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the common case of BucketCache is now to keep data blocks in L2 and leave L1 for index/bloom/meta. So this would be to populate data blocks into L2 instead of taking data on-heap when L2 is enabled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14164157" author="stack" created="Wed, 8 Oct 2014 21:01:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=anoop.hbase&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;anoop.hbase&quot;&gt;Anoop Sam John&lt;/a&gt; What Nick said and as the subject says, yeah, offheap from dfsclient via checksumming and onto the offheap BC.  This is what I want for Christmas.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14164546" author="anoop.hbase" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 01:22:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Make sense. Will wait for your results. We are now working on the readiness part to support scan to served via offheap HFileBlocks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14175830" author="stack" created="Sat, 18 Oct 2014 03:23:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We need a pread version of the HasEnhancedByteBufferAccess zero-copy methods. As is, need to seek then BB read but the seek and BB read must be under a lock/synchronize. Won&apos;t work for us unless we do the pread version (each works on its own block... no synchronizing on stream..)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14175839" author="tlipcon" created="Sat, 18 Oct 2014 04:02:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adding the ByteBuffer-based pread was always planned in HDFS &amp;#8211; we just didn&apos;t get to it. But I&apos;m sure we can get someone to do the patch it would be nice to have &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
